of shooting enjoyment.  The receiver is hand polished and enhanced with a rolled arabesque engraving pattern.  It is then protected by a silver nitride finish applied in super heated conditions that provides a corrosion resistant surface.MonoblocThe monobloc is also cut from a forged steel ingot by computerized CNC machines to similar precise dimensions.  The monobloc contains 2 locking lugs which engage the crossbolt, 2 integral shoulder lugs and a base lug which interlocks with the receiver as the action is closed.  This combination forms one of the strongest actions on the market.  The barrel tubes are seated and soldered into the monoblock to ensure the correct point of impact of both the top and bottom barrel.  Each side of the monoblock is precisely cut for a single piece ejector and the pivot seat.  The finished barrel group rotates at the pivot seat on two trunnions mounted through the sides of the receiver.  After years of use, the SKB action can be easily re-tightened if need be, ensuring that your shotgun maintains a tight fit for many more years of service.Trigger Group The non-detachable trigger system of the 85TSS has been improved with a design refinement to reduce engagement creep and over-travel.  This new tournament trigger allows the sear to disengage and drop with less pull weight.  The shooter feels a smooth and crisp trigger pull.  The hammers are powered by  “modified V” shaped springs that provide faster lock times than conventional coil springs.  The firing order of the barrels is determined by the position of the barrel selector.  The selector is located in the trigger blade keeping its operation separate from the tang mounted manual safety. The 85TSS Tournament Stocks are designed to provide the shooter with a quick handling, responsive fit.  A shotgun's "fit" is determined by the physical dimensions of the buttstock relative to the shooter's physique.  These dimensions determine how fast the shooter can mount and accurately point the shotgun at a moving target.  Stock dimensions affect how the shotgun is positioned in the shooter's hands and shoulder, against the shooter's cheek, and the alignment of the shooter's eye to the sighting plane.  Recognizing that each shotgun discipline has different requirements, and recognizing the need to "fit" our customers, tournament stocks are available in four styles; Sporting Clays, Skeet, Trap Standard and Trap Monte Carlo.  All are available with either a "fixed comb" or an "adjustable comb".  Also, a select number of models are available with High Grade Wood as an optional feature.  All 85TSS tournament stocks feature a forward sweeping pistol grip with a tight radius curve.  This places the shooter’s hand closer to the trigger and aligns the wrist in a more natural and comfortable position.  This enhances the shooter’s ability to swing and control the shotgun

title: For Sale:  9mm Smith & Wesson 3913 Excellent to near mint cond.
postcontent: 9mm Smith & Wesson 3913, Lady NL comes as shown: padded black gun case, 52- Federal 9mm 135gr Pers. Def. JHP, 134- Winchester 9mm Luger 115gr Target/Range rounds and 50- Winchester 9mm Luger 147gr Pers. Prot. rounds. Stainless Steel slide & barrel with lightweight alloy frame, wraparound grips, and 8-shot magazine (plus one in the chamber). Configured with the white Delrin grips. In lightly used condition with no issues. Suitable either as a nice concealed carry piece or as an addition to your Smith collection. The Smith and Wesson 3913 is well known for accuracy and reliability. It has an ambidextrous, slide-mounted, de-cocking/safety lever with a hammer that decocks flush to the back of the slide, a slide release lever, a magazine release, and a magazine disconnect which disables the trigger when the magazine is removed. It is thin, at barely an inch wide, making it a favorite for concealed carry.One of the best semi-auto Smith & Wesson ever made. S&W calls the 3913 “traditional double-action” or TDA. In the TDA configuration, trigger pulls. The trigger is DA first shot with following shots SA. The difference between this pistol and others claiming to be double action is that the first shot is true double action. The hammer strikes every time the trigger is pulled just like a revolver. Trigger pull is very smooth with DA pull at about 10 lbs and SA pull at about 4 lbs. A short reset allows quick follow on shots.Novak dovetailed 3 dot low profile with white dots sights. It is a single-stack 9mm. It comes with two high quality magazines that have finger-rest bases, clearly numbered index holes, with a high-contrast, orange follower and an integrated light rail for a weapon mounted light. The 3913’s grip is very thin and nice looking plastic grips and just about 1 inch wide—quite comfortable. The slide is .9 inches across, increased slightly by the width of the slide-mounted safety lever.This S&W does not have a factory key-lock, appreciated by many. It has a “loaded chamber indicator”. The Manual, Registration & Warranty paperwork is also included. S&W 3913 Specs• Action: DA/SA• Capacity: 8+1• Weight empty: 24 oz• Overall length: 6.75″• Barrel length: 3.5″• Height: 5.0″• Grip thickness: 1.0″• Sight radius: 5.5″• Safety: External safety/de-cocker lever, Magazine disconnect
